---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Install · Squeezy"
  description="Squeezy install, first-run provider selection, diagnostics, and session start."
  activeDoc="/docs/install/"
  eyebrow="install"
  heading="Choose a platform, install Squeezy, run doctor."
  lead="The install flow is platform-first: use the native package path for your OS, verify with doctor, then start Squeezy in the repository you want it to understand."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Primary install commands</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">macOS</span>
        <h3>Apple Silicon and Intel release targets</h3>
        <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/esqueezy/squeezy/main/install.sh | sh</code></pre>
        <p>Targets: `aarch64-apple-darwin`, `x86_64-apple-darwin`. Homebrew is also documented.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">Linux</span>
        <h3>x86_64 static binary</h3>
        <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/esqueezy/squeezy/main/install.sh | sh</code></pre>
        <p>Target: `x86_64-unknown-linux-musl`.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">Windows</span>
        <h3>x86_64</h3>
        <pre><code>winget install esqueezy.Squeezy</code></pre>
        <p>Target: `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc`. Manual zip install is also documented.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">source</span>
        <h3>Cargo install</h3>
        <pre><code>cargo install squeezy --locked</code></pre>
        <p>Use when you already have the required Rust toolchain.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>First run</h2>
    <pre><code>export OPENAI_API_KEY=...
squeezy doctor
squeezy</code></pre>
    <p>On first interactive startup, Squeezy can detect configured provider credentials and local Ollama availability, then save provider/model defaults without writing secret token values.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Self-investigation</h2>
    <p>Ask Squeezy about Squeezy with `/help` or natural questions such as "how does Squeezy choose providers?" Product-help questions are answered from bundled docs and redacted config before a provider call is made.</p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
